
// This Hyperlambda code uses the [validators.mandatory] slot to ensure that a "name" node exists within the "file" node, which is a child of the [.arguments] node. If the "name" node is not present, an exception will be thrown. This is useful for enforcing the presence of required arguments in a Hyperlambda script or endpoint.
validators.mandatory:x:@.arguments/*/file/*/name
